{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Fund free lens thinning and tints for people registered sight impaired",
        "additional_details": "We urge the Government to:\r\n1) Fund the maximum NHS optical voucher (Band D or H equivalent) to any individual registered as Severely Sight Impaired (Blind).\r\n2) Provide sufficient funding to ensure this maximum value fully covers all clinically prescribed lens thinning and specialist tints/filters.",
        "background": "We believe the NHS optical voucher scheme fails severely sight impaired (SSI) people. Lens upgrades (thinning/tints) cost \u00a3175-\u00a3300, draining funds that could be used for other disability costs. We want the maximum voucher for all SSI people to cover essential, clinically prescribed features fully.",
